node.text:
Today we're launching #ForzaPaintbooth as a way to celebrate the livery artists of the Forza community, and we're doing it in style with these shots from @PTG_Wildcat. 
Use #ForzaPaintbooth to show off your designs, and they might appear on our feed or even be featured in-game.

node.text: Today’s feature is @forza.horizonphoto, who had this to say: “Photography has no limits. Now mix that with your passions such as cars and your imagination is endless! Don’t be scared in expanding your capabilities, GO WILD and try new things everyday because by doing that not only do you come up with new,better techniques but you discover more and more of your own self ;) Love to you all! ✌️❤️”

node.text:
Week 1 of the #HPDForza Bounty Hunter has begun, and your first challenge is taking on Canadian Touring Car Champion @karlwittmer.

Beat his time in this week’s Rivals for an exclusive 2017 Acura NSX livery, Acura driver gear, and up to 1,000,000 in-game credits. Get to racing!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Forza Motorsport on September 07, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎MOTORSPORT RIVALS PREVIEW SEPTEMBER Return to the Ring OCTOBER Bad to the Bone want my Mummy OVEMBER One to Celebrate Rodeo is in Town DECEMBER Forza Ugly Sweater Party Forza Bounty Hunter Streamer Edition יק MOTORSPORT FORZA‎'‎.

node.text:
The party isn't stopping anytime soon!

While we still have time before Forza Motorsport 7 is delisted, we wanted to share a sneak peek of some of the Rivals Events you can look forward to. Trust us, there's a lot more where that's coming from.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Forza Motorsport on September 07, 2021. May be an image of car.

node.text: Only a few more days before Forza Motorsport 7 is delisted, and we're celebrating the game in @ForzaHorizon 4! Download the game from @XboxGamePass to get this special livery in your inbox tomorrow, September 8th.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Forza Motorsport on September 07, 2021 tagging @paduffel. May be an image of car and road.

node.text: We're spotlighting @Paduffel today, who had this to say: "The most important thing about photography is that you have fun with it and that you enjoy your own work. You can push yourself and always try to get better, but only do this for yourself and not to prove something to others."

node.text:
In honor of a friend, avid Motorsport player, and father to a dear colleague we wanted to share this livery with our community. 

Known to many as SPC Geezer, one of his favorite accomplishments was his Top 200 Class A record in the New York Circuit on FM2. Today we share this in celebration of his life in and out of gaming.

node.text: Check out these shots from @jspxrr featuring our 2020 Special Olympics livery. Here's what @jspxrr has to share with the photo community: "Make sure your photos look good for yourself first, others can wait. If you really like somebody's photo and wish you could make that, practice making similar to it, because it's progression too! Don't be afraid if your photos look like copying, it can be a hard work to get to a point of someone's level. Inspiration is everything!"
